OL,3,CHow the Home Office plans to stop
OL,4,Cforeign sex offenders claiming UK
OL,5,Casylum
OL,7,FHome Secretary Yvette Cooper said "it
OL,8,Fis wrong" there have been cases of
OL,9,Fcriminals, such as the Clapham
OL,10,Fchemical attacker, who have been
OL,11,Fgranted asylum despite their
OL,12,Fconviction.
OL,14,FThe government hopes this will send a
OL,15,Fclear message that sex offences are
OL,16,Ftreated with the "seriousness they
OL,17,Fdeserve", while the Tories called the
OL,18,Fmeasures "too little too late".
