OL,7,FWhat is the law currently and how will
OL,8,Fit change?
OL,10,FThe Refugee Convention gives countries
OL,11,Fthe powers to refuse asylum to
OL,12,Fterrorists, war criminals and people
OL,13,Fconvicted of a "particularly serious
OL,14,Fcrime" who present a danger to the
OL,15,Fcommunity.
OL,17,FIn the UK, that is categorised by a
OL,18,Fcriminal who has been handed a prison
OL,19,Fsentence of one year or more.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/22
