OL,4,Cforeign sex offenders claiming UK
OL,5,Casylum
OL,7,FHe avoided jail and was handed a
OL,8,Fsuspended sentence. He was put on the
OL,9,FSex Offenders Register for 10 years
OL,10,Fand ordered to carry out 200 hours of
OL,11,Funpaid work.
OL,13,FIt is believed Ezedi, from
OL,14,FAfghanistan, travelled to the UK on a
OL,15,Florry in 2016. But it is understood
OL,16,Fhis asylum claims were rejected twice
OL,17,Fby the Home Office.
OL,19,FHe was convicted two years after his
OL,20,Ffirst claim was rejected by the Home
OL,21,FOffice.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/22
