OL,3,CHow the Home Office plans to stop
OL,4,Cforeign sex offenders claiming UK
OL,5,Casylum
OL,7,FThe Conservatives have argued the
OL,8,Fgovernment's change wouldn't stop a
OL,9,Fmigrant convicted of sex offences from
OL,10,Fusing the European Convention on Human
OL,11,FRights to block their removal from the
OL,12,FUK.
OL,14,FAsked whether this is the case, she
OL,15,Ftold ITV News: "Well, the first step
OL,16,Fwe're taking is to strengthen the law
OL,17,Fso that we can prevent people who are
OL,18,Fon sex offender registers from being
OL,19,Fgranted asylum protection in this
OL,20,Fcountry. They should not be given
OL,21,Frefugee status.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G14/22
