OL,3,CHow the Home Office plans to stop
OL,4,Cforeign sex offenders claiming UK
OL,5,Casylum
OL,7,F"They should not be being given the
OL,8,Fkinds of protection that asylum gives
OL,9,Fto people who have fled persecution
OL,10,Fand conflict.
OL,12,F"Then we're also increasing
OL,13,Fdeportations and returns, including
OL,14,Fenforced returns, up by more than 20%
OL,15,Fsince the election alone.
OL,17,F"Wherever there are challenges to
OL,18,Fdeportation and removal, we will be
OL,19,Frobust in our response to those
OL,20,Fbecause we think that is the right
OL,21,Fthing to do."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G15/22
